  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vietnamese ethnic minority household economies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Funds are provided to (1) Support the Government of Vietnam&#x2019;s National poverty reduction programme, P135, targeted in poor ethnic minority communities promoting local level economic development. (2) Provide multi-annual support to a small number of agencies working in the targeted provinces (Helen Keller, Plan International,Care International, Oxfam Vietnam, RIC and UN Women) to pilot and scale up new models in ethnic minority empowerment: their focus will be on voice and participation, integrated nutrition response, gender empowerment and climate-sensitive development.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vietnamese ethnic minority household economies grown in a climate-smart, gender-and nutrition-sensitive way</narrative>
  </description>
